<TITLE> Missing woman's body found in capital </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 14 (bdnews24.com)Police Monday said they had recovered the decomposed body of a housewife, a week after she was reported missing in the capital. Kadamtali police station arrested a woman in connection with the incident. Police and relatives of the deceased, Shirin Akhter, 35, said she had gone out of her house on Sept 7 and her body tied with rope in a sack was found in a manhole in the city's Dakshin Dania area. Sub-Inspector Mahbubur Rahman told bdnews24.com that Shirin, wife of a Saudi expatriate, used to lend people money on interest. On Sept 7, Shirin from her Muktodhara residential house went to see one of her borrowers, Lipi Rahman, who took Tk 16,000 from her, police said, adding that the manhole is close to Lipi's house. Shirin's daughter, Nishi accused Lipi and her associates of murdering her mother. bdn
